The paper deals with the problem of learning the optimal structure of a Bayesian network, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed algorithm also involves memory-efficient search techniques, which are relevant to data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). Finally, the problem of learning Bayesian networks is also relevant to systems and control (cs.SY).
